  "prompt": "What are all the records broken on Twitter?",
  "response": "Twitter, now known as X since October 2023, has been around for quite some time and has witnessed several records in various categories over the years. Here are some notable records broken on the platform:\n\n1. **Most Retweeted Tweet**: Ellen DeGeneres' Oscars selfie from 2014 held the record for the most retweeted tweet for a significant period. However, this record was later surpassed by Carter Wilkerson's tweet in 2017, where he asked Wendy's for free chicken nuggets.\n\n2. **Most Followed Account**: As of recent years, the account with the most followers has been that of former U.S. President Barack Obama.\n\n3. **Fastest Growing Account**: When Lionel Messi joined Paris Saint-Germain (PSG) in August 2021, his announcement tweet became one of the fastest-growing tweets in terms of interactions.\n\n4. **Most Tweets Per Second**: This record is often broken during major global events. The 2014 FIFA World Cup, particularly the final match, saw an enormous number of tweets per second.\n\n5. **Longest Tweet with Most Characters**: Originally, tweets were limited to 140 characters, then expanded to 280 characters. Any tweets that are longer than this are not typical and can't be considered for record purposes.\n\nPlease note that records can change frequently due to new users and events. For more updated records, you may want to refer directly to Twitter's statistics or platforms that track social media analytics.",
